A 38-year old man has died during a service delivery protest in Kariega in the Eastern Cape. eNCA's Nceba Ntlanganiso reports. #DStv403 KWANOBUHLE - A 38-year old man has died during a service delivery protest in Kariega in the Eastern Cape. Protesters took their anger to the streets in the early hours of Thursday morning. Two vehicles, an Algoa bus and a councillor's house were set alight. The protesters say it's been four years since they were promised housing plots, electricity and water in their informal settlement. The Nelson Mandela Bay municipality says its aware of the issues and is working on them. * eNCA's Nceba Ntlanganiso reports.